      "title": "Map showing Mahadayi river along with its riparian states",
      "description": "River basin boundaries are plotted in bold gray curves. The\r\nGoa state boundary is plotted as a black curve and the Karnataka-Maharashtra state boundary as a yellow curve. The greenish curve\r\nrunning from top to bottom east of the Goa-Karnataka boundary is the meteorological ridge separating the windward and leeward sides.\r\nThe background colour is used to highlight distinct areas of the Mahadayi river basin and the adjacent river basins. The Mahadayi river\r\nbasin is divided into five sub-regions: freshwater and salt-water regimes in Goa,windward and leeward sides of the ridge in Karnataka, and\r\nthe sub-basin in Maharashtra. Other adjacent river basins (where various water transfer projects have been planned) are also highlighted:\r\nKalinadi or Kali basin, Malaprabha basin, Chapora (Tillari) basin, and Zuari basin. Towns, dams in Goa and the proposed dams, wildlife\r\nsanctuaries and national parks, the state-border crossing points for the streams, the limit of tidal incursion or the freshwater limiting point,\r\nand water treatment plants.",
